    <title>双指针</title>
    <link href="https://huangpiao.tech/2024/11/15/algorithm/%E5%8F%8C%E6%8C%87%E9%92%88/"/>
    <id>https://huangpiao.tech/2024/11/15/algorithm/%E5%8F%8C%E6%8C%87%E9%92%88/</id>
    <published>2024-11-14T16:00:00.000Z</published>
    <updated>2025-04-18T05:02:25.809Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>​<strong>双指针算法</strong>（Two-pointer technique）是一种常用的算法技巧，通常用来优化处理线性结构（如数组或链表）的问题。其基本思想是使用两个指针同时遍历数据结构，通常一个指针从左往右移动，另一个指针从右往左移动，或者两个指针一起从左到右遍历。双指针算法在解决一些问题时能够显著降低时间复杂度，特别是在解决 <strong>排序数组</strong>、<strong>滑动窗口</strong> 或 <strong>链表</strong> 等问题时非常有效。</p><span id="more"></span><h4 id="双指针算法的应用场景"><a href="#双指针算法的应用场景" class="headerlink" title="双指针算法的应用场景"></a>双指针算法的应用场景</h4><ol><li><strong>有序数组&#x2F;链表中查找问题</strong>： 双指针常常用来在一个有序数组中寻找两个数的和等于给定值的情况（例如“两数之和”问题）。</li><li><strong>滑动窗口问题</strong>： 用两个指针标记窗口的起始和结束位置，通过调整窗口的大小来满足某些条件。</li><li><strong>快慢指针</strong>： 一个指针慢速移动，一个指针快速移动，可以用来解决如链表环检测、求中点等问题。</li></ol><h5 id="常见的双指针问题与技巧"><a href="#常见的双指针问题与技巧" class="headerlink" title="常见的双指针问题与技巧"></a>常见的双指针问题与技巧</h5><h6 id="1-两数之和-Two-Sum"><a href="#1-两数之和-Two-Sum" class="headerlink" title="1. 两数之和 (Two Sum)"></a>1. <strong>两数之和 (Two Sum)</strong></h6><ul><li>问题：给定一个排序数组，找出数组中两个数之和为目标值。</li><li>解法：使用双指针，左指针从数组的起始位置开始，右指针从数组的末尾开始。如果两数和小于目标值，左指针向右移动；如果两数和大于目标值，右指针向左移动，直到找到结果。</li></ul><figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title function_">twoSum</span>(<span class="params">arr, target</span>):</span><br><span class="line">    left, right = <span class="number">0</span>, <span class="built_in">len</span>(arr) - <span class="number">1</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">while</span> left &lt; right:</span><br><span class="line">        current_sum = arr[left] + arr[right]</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">if</span> current_sum == target:</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="keyword">return</span> [arr[left], arr[right]]</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">elif</span> current_sum &lt; target:</span><br><span class="line">            left += <span class="number">1</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">else</span>:</span><br><span class="line">            right -= <span class="number">1</span></span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="literal">None</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h6 id="2-Shortest-Subarray-to-be-Removed-to-Make-Array-Sorted"><a href="#2-Shortest-Subarray-to-be-Removed-to-Make-Array-Sorted" class="headerlink" title="2. Shortest Subarray to be Removed to Make Array Sorted"></a>2. Shortest Subarray to be Removed to Make Array Sorted</h6><p>Given an integer array <code>arr</code>, remove a subarray (can be empty) from <code>arr</code> such that the remaining elements in <code>arr</code> are <strong>non-decreasing</strong>.</p><p>Return <em>the length of the shortest subarray to remove</em>.</p><p>A <strong>subarray</strong> is a contiguous subsequence of the array.</p><p><strong>Example 1:</strong></p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">Input: arr = [1,2,3,10,4,2,3,5]</span><br><span class="line">Output: 3</span><br><span class="line">Explanation: The shortest subarray we can remove is [10,4,2] of length 3. The remaining elements after that will be [1,2,3,3,5] <span class="built_in">which</span> are sorted.</span><br><span class="line">Another correct solution is to remove the subarray [3,10,4].</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br><span class="line">17</span><br><span class="line">18</span><br><span class="line">19</span><br><span class="line">20</span><br><span class="line">21</span><br><span class="line">22</span><br><span class="line">23</span><br><span class="line">24</span><br><span class="line">25</span><br><span class="line">26</span><br><span class="line">27</span><br><span class="line">28</span><br><span class="line">29</span><br><span class="line">30</span><br><span class="line">31</span><br><span class="line">32</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">class</span> <span class="title class_">Solution</span>:</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="keyword">def</span> <span class="title function_">findLengthOfShortestSubarray</span>(<span class="params">self, arr</span>):</span><br><span class="line">        n = <span class="built_in">len</span>(arr)</span><br><span class="line">        </span><br><span class="line">        <span class="comment"># Step 1: Find the longest non-decreasing prefix</span></span><br><span class="line">        prefix_end = <span class="number">0</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">while</span> prefix_end &lt; n - <span class="number">1</span> <span class="keyword">and</span> arr[prefix_end] &lt;= arr[prefix_end + <span class="number">1</span>]:</span><br><span class="line">            prefix_end += <span class="number">1</span></span><br><span class="line">        </span><br><span class="line">        <span class="comment"># If the whole array is non-decreasing, no need to remove anything</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">if</span> prefix_end == n - <span class="number">1</span>:</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="keyword">return</span> <span class="number">0</span></span><br><span class="line">        </span><br><span class="line">        <span class="comment"># Step 2: Find the longest non-decreasing suffix</span></span><br><span class="line">        suffix_start = n - <span class="number">1</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">while</span> suffix_start &gt; <span class="number">0</span> <span class="keyword">and</span> arr[suffix_start] &gt;= arr[suffix_start - <span class="number">1</span>]:</span><br><span class="line">            suffix_start -= <span class="number">1</span></span><br><span class="line">        </span><br><span class="line">        <span class="comment"># Step 3: Try to remove the subarray by merging prefix and suffix</span></span><br><span class="line">        <span class="comment"># Case where we remove the suffix or prefix</span></span><br><span class="line">        ans = <span class="built_in">min</span>(n - prefix_end - <span class="number">1</span>, suffix_start)  </span><br><span class="line">        </span><br><span class="line">        <span class="comment"># Step 4: Try merging the prefix and suffix</span></span><br><span class="line">        i, j = <span class="number">0</span>, suffix_start</span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">while</span> i &lt;= prefix_end <span class="keyword">and</span> j &lt; n:</span><br><span class="line">            <span class="keyword">if</span> arr[i] &lt;= arr[j]:</span><br><span class="line">                ans = <span class="built_in">min</span>(ans, j - i - <span class="number">1</span>)</span><br><span class="line">                i += <span class="number">1</span></span><br><span class="line">            <span class="keyword">else</span>:</span><br><span class="line">                j += <span class="number">1</span></span><br><span class="line">        </span><br><span class="line">        <span class="keyword">return</span> ans</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>]]></content>
    
    
    <summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;​	&lt;strong&gt;双指针算法&lt;/strong&gt;（Two-pointer technique）是一种常用的算法技巧，通常用来优化处理线性结构（如数组或链表）的问题。其基本思想是使用两个指针同时遍历数据结构，通常一个指针从左往右移动，另一个指针从右往左移动，或者两个指针一起从左到右遍历。双指针算法在解决一些问题时能够显著降低时间复杂度，特别是在解决 &lt;strong&gt;排序数组&lt;/strong&gt;、&lt;strong&gt;滑动窗口&lt;/strong&gt; 或 &lt;strong&gt;链表&lt;/strong&gt; 等问题时非常有效。&lt;/p&gt;</summary>
    
    
    
